Im trying to use elastic to extract brands from a texts. For this I created a index containing brands a synonyms where the synonyms are analysed as keywords. I then search for brand with shingles (scripts to reproduce is below). This works great in elastic version 2.4.4. When I try this in elastic 5.4.3 it doesn't work at all, I looked at the data with the analyze endpoint and it looks like it should work.

Had a disussion about how shingles work here: https://discuss.elastic.co/t/extracting-brands-in-documents-using-keyword-and-shingles/91873.

We agreed that this is a regression for elastic 5.4.3.

Scripts to reproduce:

```
PUT brand
{
  "settings": {
    "analysis": {
      "analyzer": {
        "my_analyzer_keyword": {
          "type": "custom",
          "tokenizer": "keyword",
          "filter": [
            "asciifolding",
            "lowercase"
          ]
        },
        "my_analyzer_shingle": {
          "type": "custom",
          "tokenizer": "standard",
          "filter": [
            "asciifolding",
            "lowercase",
            "shingle"
